headline: Chocolate Maker Hershey Expects Sweeter 2026, Hikes Dividend
summary: The Hershey Company (NYSE:HSY) posted stronger-than-expected quarterly results on Thursday, with solid net sales growth despite volume pressure tied to consumer price sensitivity. The company flagged ongoing margin headwinds from elevated commodity and tariff costs and higher operating expenses, even as shares rose in premarket trading. Hershey reported fourth-quarter adjusted earnings per share of $1.71, beating the analyst consensus estimate of $1.40. Quarterly sales of $3.09 billion (+7% year
